<section xmlns="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/dc-library" xmlns:codified="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codified" xmlns:codify="https://code.dccouncil.us/schemas/codify" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" containing-doc="D.C. Code">
  <num>24-467</num>
  <heading>Exceptions.</heading>
  <text>Persons convicted of first degree murder or persons sentenced for crimes committed when armed under <cite path="§22-4502">§ 22-4502</cite>, or under <cite path="§22-4504|(b)">§ 22-4504(b)</cite>, or under <cite path="§22-2803">§ 22-2803</cite>, shall not be eligible for geriatric parole or geriatric suspension of sentence.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 9-271" type="History" path="§8">May 15, 1993, D.C. Law 9-271, § 8, 40 DCR 792</annotation>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 10-68" type="History">Feb. 5, 1994, D.C. Law 10-68, § 57, 40 DCR 6311</annotation>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 10-255" type="History">May 16, 1995, D.C. Law 10-255, § 18, 41 DCR 5193</annotation>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 10-258" type="History">May 25, 1995, D.C. Law 10-258, § 2, 42 DCR 238</annotation>
    <annotation doc="D.C. Law 19-318" type="History">June 15, 2013, D.C. Law 19-318, § 2(a), 59 DCR 12469</annotation>
    <annotation type="Effect of Amendments">The 2013 amendment by <cite doc="D.C. Law 19-318">D.C. Law 19-318</cite> substituted “or under <cite path="§22-2803">§ 22-2803</cite>” for “and <cite path="§22-2803">§ 22-2803</cite>”; and substituted “eligible for geriatric parole or geriatric suspension of sentence” for “eligible for geriatric or medical parole.”</annotation>
